 epic drop or 2.<br>level Range - 35+ <br>Approximate length of - As long as people would like to stick around.<br><br>I would like to find a tracker who would be willing to come along with us for this trip.  A zone such as BW is easier to hunt with a tracker.  So if anyone is interested pls let me know.  <br><br>Loot and Epic drops - I will ML and split the loot after.  I am not calling anything for this.  If we get any epic drops everyone who needs it will random 3x level.   <br><br>Battle plan:  First we will invis at the zone and go to the giant fort and pull to there.  We will begin slow and step up the pace as we become accustom to hunting together.  We will have the tracker pull to us and pets will take over.  <br><br>I would like to see at least 2 earth pets to tank, a lvl 52 fire pet for dmg and the fact he will DS all other pets in the grp; as well as, air pet for the stun.  The only 2 pets taunting will be the earth pets -- all other pets will have taunt turned off.  This is only one of the possible combination of pets and we will experiement with others.   Please make sure you have have hot keys for pet attack, pet back off, pet taunt and pet no taunt and pet get lost.  <br><br>Who has and is able to use Transon's Elemental Infusion (lvl 52)?  This is a great heal spell for pet and a life saver for a tanking pet.  <br><br>We will pull just about everything skellys, apes, giants, wurms the only thing I want to stay away from at first is gullerback.  Once we get into a good stride we can start looking for the named we need for our epic.  <br><br>Please sign up, so that I will have an idea of who can go.  While we have about 5 mages active, any of the mages in the guild are welcome to attend.  <br><br>Symira<br>53 Mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ujoseydm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Josey DM</A></span><br> <span class=userti